0survived%20them%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEuglenoids%20are%20microscopic%20life%20forms%20that%20combine%20both%20animal%20and%20plant%20traits%2C%26quot%3B%20Bas%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%2C%20a%20geosciences%20professor%20at%20Utrecht%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20via%20email.%20They%20eat%20like%20animals%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fextreme-heat-climate-change-stop-tropical-trees-photosynthesis-kill-plants-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephotosynthesize%20like%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20find%20the%20organisms%20in%20freshwater%20ponds%20all%20around%20the%20globe%2C%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%20said.%20But%20they're%20rarely%20found%20in%20the%20fossil%20record%2C%20even%20though%20they've%20been%20around%20for%20eras.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20find%20ancient%20evidence%20of%20euglenoids%2C%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%20and%20his%20colleagues%20looked%20at%20microfossils%20%E2%80%94%20teensy%20fossils%20that%20are%20only%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmanoa.hawaii.edu%2Fexploringourfluidearth%2Fphysical%2Focean-floor%2Foceanic-crust-and-seafloor%2Fweird-science-oceanic-microfossils%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efew%20millimeters%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20worked%20on%20a%20hunch%20that%20these%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foldest-fossils-life-hydrothermal-vents-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicrofossils%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20cysts%20of%20euglenoids%2C%20but%20no%20one%20had%20ever%20seen%20a%20euglenoid%20make%20a%20cyst%20in%20nature%20or%20in%20a%20lab%2C%26quot%3B%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDating%20back%20400%20million%20years%2C%20some%20euglenoids%20made%20cysts%20that%20protected%20the%20organism%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthese-7-animals-have-crazy-adaptations-to-help-them-to-survive-in-their-habitats-2016-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunfavorable%20conditions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20it%20was%20unclear%20what%20these%20cysts%20looked%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20chance%20viewing%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dwytez4cAjb8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EYouTube%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20video%20helped%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%20and%20his%20colleagues%20link%20the%20fossils%20and%20living%20euglenoids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20finding%20could%20help%20establish%20euglenoids%20as%20some%20of%20the%20earliest%20ancestors%20of%20all%20living%20plants%20and%20animals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20proof%20was%20in%20a%20pond%20(and%20on%20YouTube)%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20two%20main%20problems%20with%20the%20cyst%20microfossils%3A%20what%20they%20were%20called%20and%20what%20they%20looked%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20working%20in%20different%20time%20slices%20had%20basically%20given%20different%20names%20to%20the%20same%20kind%20of%20microfossils%2C%20obscuring%20their%20long%20evolutionary%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20Paleozoic%20Chomotriletes%2C%20Mesozoic%20Pseudoschizaea%2C%20and%20Cenozoic%20Concentricystes.%20The%20researchers%20went%20through%20500%20papers%20to%20find%20mentions%20of%20all%20the%20different%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20scientists%20had%20noticed%20the%20similarities%20between%20all%20these%20microfossils%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bthe%20cysts%20have%20a%20structure%20that%20is%20unlike%20anything%20that%20has%20been%20seen%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%20said.%20Since%20no%20one%20had%20ever%20documented%20a%20euglenoid%20making%20a%20cyst%2C%20there%20was%20nothing%20from%20the%20present%20to%20compare%20the%20ancient%20examples%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20one%20of%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge's%20co-authors%2C%20Paul%20Strother%2C%20Googled%20%26quot%3BEuglena%20cysts%26quot%3B%20and%20a%20result%20on%20YouTube%20popped%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20video%2C%20Fabian%20Weston%20was%20showing%20a%20sample%20of%20pond%20water%20under%20a%20microscope.%20The%20New%20South%20Wales%20resident%20has%20a%20YouTube%20channel%20devoted%20to%20filming%20all%20sorts%20of%20microscopic%20organisms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20video%20below%2C%20you%20can%20see%20the%20Euglena%20form%20into%20a%20ball%20with%20a%20thick%2C%20ribbed%20wall.%20%26quot%3BThe%20cysts%20look%20layered%2C%20and%20this%20may%20be%20constructed%20from%20the%20mucus%20that%20is%20typically%20on%20the%20outside%20of%20certain%20euglenoids%2C%26quot%3B%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2Fwytez4cAjb8%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Euglena%20Encystment%20-%20A%20Rarely%20Seen%20Event%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20watching%20it%2C%20we%20were%20convinced%20that%20what%20was%20seen%20in%20the%20video%20is%20Euglena%20making%20the%20kind%20of%20structure%20we%20see%20as%20microfossils%2C%26quot%3B%20van%20de%20Schootbrugge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20missing%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20we%20did%2C%20really%2C%20was%20to%20make%20the%20connection%20with%20the%20most%20recently%20living%20forms%2C%20which%20tied%20the%20taxonomic%20names%20to%20the%20living%20microorganisms%2C%26quot%3B%20Strother%20told%20Business%20Insider%20via%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20recently%20published%20their%20paper%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS0034666723002129%3Fvia%253Dihub%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EReview%20of%20Palaeobotany%20and%20Palynology%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVan%20de%20Schootbrugge%20noted%20that%20they%20haven't%20yet%20seen%20Weston's%20cysts%20themselves%20and%20hope%20to%20go%20look%20at%20the%20pond's%20sediment%20for%20Chomotrilete%20microfossils.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20evolutionary%20tree%20of%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStrother%20thinks%20this%20study%20is%20a%20piece%20of%20the%20puzzle%20regarding%20the%20eukaryotic%20Tree%20of%20Life%20(eTOL).%20Eukaryotes%20are%20the%20domain%20of%20organisms%20that%20all%20animals%20and%20plants%20belong%20to.%20Unlike%20bacteria%2C%20their%20cells%20have%20a%20nucleus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20they're%20some%20of%20our%20earliest%20eukaryotic%20ancestors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20think%20euglenoids%20could%20have%20evolved%20over%20a%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uu.nl%2Fen%2Fnews%2Fmicrofossils-shed-light-on-the-long-fossil-record-of-euglenoids%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20study.%20Knowing%20which%20eukaryotes%20evolved%20first%20would%20be%20a%20huge%20step%20in%20understanding%20how%20they've%20survived%20for%20so%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221557%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black-and-white%20image%20of%20euglenoid%20cyst%20magnified%20showing%20its%20unusual%20structure%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bd674343bb77284ba3445c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22876%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20unusual%20wall%20structure%20of%20a%20Holocene%20euglenoid%20cyst%20from%20Lake%20Vouliagmeni%2C%20Greece.%3Cp%3EWilson%20Taylor%2FUniversity%20of%20Wisconsin%2C%20Eau%20Claire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EExtending%20euglenoids'%20fossil%20records%20this%20far%20back%20in%20geological%20time%20suggests%20that%20they're%20among%20the%20oldest%20eukaryotes%2C%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EStrother%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%