0the%20Louisville%20merchant%20physically%20and%20mentally%20abused%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20debt%20reasons%2C%20Wood%20was%20sold%20again%20as%20a%20teenager%20to%20a%20French%20immigrant%2C%20William%20Cirode%2C%20between%201835%20and%201848%20in%20New%20Orleans%2C%20where%20she%20worked%20as%20a%20housemaid.%20When%20Cirode%20abandoned%20his%20family%20due%20to%20legal%20issues%2C%20his%20wife%2C%20Jane%2C%20moved%20back%20to%20Cincinnati%2C%20where%20she%20rented%20out%20Wood%20as%20a%20domestic%20servant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EShort-lived%20freedom%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFearing%20debt%20collectors%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fhenrietta-wood-sued-reparations-won-180972845%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJane%20Cirode%20declared%20Wood%20free%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20an%20Ohio%20courthouse%20in%201848.%20This%20legally%20meant%20Wood%20could%20work%20as%20a%20free%20Black%20woman.%20She%20remembered%20that%20period%20of%20her%20life%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pulitzer.org%2Fwinners%2Fw-caleb-mcdaniel%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esweet%20taste%20of%20liberty%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20freedom%20was%20short-lived.%20Five%20years%20later%2C%20Zebulon%20Ward%2C%20a%20Kentuckian%20deputy%20sheriff%20who%20Cirode's%20daughter%20and%20son-in-law%2C%20Josephine%20and%20Robert%20White%2C%20hired%20to%20capture%20Wood%20in%20Kentucky%2C%20kidnapped%20her.%20Wood%20was%20once%20again%20enslaved%20%26quot%3Billegally%26quot%3B%20for%2016%20years%20through%20the%20Civil%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20historic%20win%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Wood's%20return%20to%20Cincinnati%20in%201870%2C%20she%20sued%20Ward%20for%20%2420%2C000%20in%20damages%20and%20lost%20wages%2C%20estimating%20that%20her%20cost%20of%20labor%20was%20worth%20%24500%20for%20every%20year%20she%20was%20enslaved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20she%20faced%20many%20hurdles%2C%20Wood%20ultimately%20won%20her%20case%20eight%20years%20after%20filing%20the%20lawsuit.%20In%201878%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F09%2F04%2Fopinion%2Fhenrietta-wood-reparations-slavery.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eall-white%20jury%20voted%20in%20Wood's%20favor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20historic%20victory%20in%20the%20history%20of%20reparations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Ward%20was%20ordered%20to%20pay%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F09%2F04%2Fopinion%2Fhenrietta-wood-reparations-slavery.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242%2C500%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20original%20amount%20Wood%20requested%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20yet%20still%20the%20largest%20sum%20a%20US%20court%20had%20ever%20awarded%20for%20reparations.%20What%20was%20%242%2C500%20in%201878%20would%20be%20worth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fhenrietta-wood-sued-reparations-won-180972845%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%20%2475%2C000%20today%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHope%20for%20a%20better%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWood%20died%20in%20Chicago%20in%201912.%20Her%20story%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20victories%20in%20the%20history%20of%20reparations%20in%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20April%201878%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesmachine.nytimes.com%2Ftimesmachine%2F1878%2F04%2F21%2F80681330.html%3Fzoom%3D14.42%26pageNumber%3D6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20Wood's%20lawsuit%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20suggested%20that%20more%20formerly%20enslaved%20Americans%20may%20ask%20for%20reparations.%20%26quot%3BThe%20United%20States%20Government%20may%20be%20asked%20to%20make%20good%20the%20loss%20of%20those%20whose%20property%20was%20suddenly%20clothed%20with%20the%20right%20of%20manhood%2C%26quot%3B%20The%20Times%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20who%20will%20recompense%20the%20millions%20of%20men%20and%20women%20for%20the%20years%20of%20liberty%20of%20which%20they%20have%20been%20defrauded%3F%20Who%20will%20make%20good%20to%20the%20thousands%20of%20kidnapped%20freemen%20the%20agony%2C%20distress%2C%20and%20bondage%20of%20a%20lifetime%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWood%20used%20the%20money%20from%20the%20lawsuit%20to%20move%20to%20Chicago%20with%20her%20son.%20The%20money%20helped%20him%20buy%20a%20home%20and%20attend%20college.%20In%201889%2C%20Wood's%20son%20became%20one%20of%20the%20first%20Black%20men%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fhenrietta-wood-sued-reparations-won-180972845%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egraduate%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20what%20would%20later%20become%20Northwestern%20University's%20School%20of%20Law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20book%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Da550b6c0f7b2aea67422f8900aea164eb5d0ccb42fdc3ac7d455a04725c4bdb1%26postID%3D65be76cbecccec890288b59e%26postSlug%3Dblack-woman-sued-her-enslaver-for-reparations-and-won-1870-2024-2%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FSweet-Taste-Liberty-Slavery-Restitution%252Fdp%252F0190846992%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESweet%20Taste%20of%20Liberty%3A%20A%20True%20Story%20of%20Slavery%20and%20Restitution%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20W.%20Caleb%20McDaniel%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Rice%20University%2C%20wrote%20that%20Wood's%20case%20stood%20as%20proof%20of%20the%20lasting%20impact%20reparations%20could%20have%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20about%20what%20former%20slaves%20were%20owed%20%E2%80%A6%20as%20well%20about%20the%20real%20differences%20restitution%20could%20make.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDanielle%20Blackman%2C%20a%20descendant%20of%20Wood%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seattletimes.com%2Fnation-world%2Fnation%2Fshe-sued-her-enslaver-for-reparations-and-won-her-descendants-never-knew%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESeattle%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Wood's%20story%20inspired%20her%20to%20pursue%20college%20and%2C%2