dow-casting%20apartment%20buildings.%20Higher%20density%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.planetizen.com%2Fnode%2F80084%2Fnimby-obstruction-and-density-paradox%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethey%20argue%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20will%20alter%20the%20character%20of%20their%20neighborhoods%20and%20hurt%20their%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20clearly%20need%20to%20increase%20density%2C%20especially%20near%20transit%2C%20to%20provide%20enough%20homes%20for%20everybody%2C%20but%20there's%20this%20deep-seated%2C%20long-existing%20distrust%20of%20density%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tristan%20Cleveland%2C%20an%20urban%20planner%20and%20researcher%20at%20the%20Canadian%20design%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhappycities.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHappy%20Cities%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadmin.happycities.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FMy-home-my-neighbourhood-wellbeing-study-111723.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20recent%20study%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Cleveland%20and%20his%20colleagues%20aimed%20to%20determine%20how%20density%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20other%20aspects%20of%20the%20built%20environment%2C%20like%20housing%20type%C2%A0%E2%80%94%C2%A0impact%20individual%20happiness%20and%20well-being.%20The%20research%2C%20which%20involved%20surveying%20almost%201%2C900%20people%20living%20in%2015%20municipalities%20in%20the%20Vancouver%20region%20of%20British%20Columbia%2C%20found%20no%20evidence%20that%20higher-density%20living%20is%20associated%20with%20decreased%20happiness%2C%20social%20connection%2C%20or%20well-being.%20Instead%2C%20it%20found%20that%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20density%20is%20necessary%2C%20but%20not%20sufficient%2C%20to%20maximize%20residents'%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell-designed%20density%20%E2%80%94%20think%20pedestrian-friendly%20streets%20with%20easy%20access%20to%20transit%20and%20amenities%20like%20shops%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20parks%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0was%20positively%20correlated%20with%20well-being%20and%20happiness.%20But%20poorly%20designed%20density%20%E2%80%94%20like%20very%20small%20apartments%2C%20scarce%20green%20space%2C%20and%20wide%20roads%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0is%20correlated%20with%20decreased%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20simply%20put%20a%20bunch%20of%20apartment%20towers%20together%20without%20providing%20things%20that%20density%20makes%20possible%2C%20such%20as%20local%20amenities%2C%20shops%2C%20transit%2C%20then%20you're%20actually%20not%20delivering%20the%20value%20of%20density%20for%20wellbeing%2C%26quot%3B%20Cleveland%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-blame-loneliness-on-housing-affordability-crisis-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20found%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20living%20in%20walkable%20neighborhoods%2C%20spending%20less%20time%20driving%20and%20commuting%2C%20and%20having%20access%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-epidemic-decline-in-third-places-friends-parks-community-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eto%20third%20places%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20coffee%20shops%20and%20parks%20are%20associated%20with%20better%20well-being%20and%20social%20connectedness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20have%20everything%20we%20need%20close%20to%20home%2C%20that%20ends%20up%20saving%20us%20a%20lot%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Madeleine%20Hebert%2C%20a%20housing%20specialist%20at%20Happy%20Cities%20who%20co-authored%20the%20firm's%20report.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20save%20time%2C%20we%20have%20more%20time%20to%20spend%20with%20our%20families%2C%20we%20have%20time%20to%20exercise%2C%20we%20have%20time%20to%20build%20social%20connections%20with%20our%20neighbors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20a%20neighborhood%20to%20support%20mass%20transit%2C%20and%20amenities%20like%20local%20shops%20and%20restaurants%2C%20it%20needs%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20density.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDensity%20is%20necessary%2C%20but%20not%20sufficient%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20across%20North%20America%20aren't%20just%20worried%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2022%2F01%2F18%2Fa-growing-share-of-americans-say-affordable-housing-is-a-major-problem-where-they-live%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehow%20expensive%20their%20neighborhoods%20are%20becoming%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20also%20looking%20for%20a%20sense%20of%20belonging.%20After%20affordability%2C%20respondents%20to%20the%20Happy%20Cities%20survey%20listed%20proximity%20to%20friends%20and%20family%20and%20%26quot%3Ba%20neighborhood%20feel%20or%20sense%20of%20community%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20top%20elements%20missing%20from%20their%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2040%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20chose%20to%20live%20in%20their%20neighborhood%20because%20of%20its%20proximity%20to%20social%20and%20recreational%20amenities%2C%20like%20restaurants%2C%20shops%2C%20and%20parks.%20That's%20compared%20to%20just%2028%25%20who%20prioritized%20being%20close%20to%20work%2C%20and%2019%25%20who%20prioritized%20proximity%20to%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20all%20comes%20at%20a%20cost.%20An%20analysis%20published%20last%20year%20found%20that%20homebuyers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartgrowthamerica.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2FFoot-Traffic-Ahead-2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ein%20the%2035%20biggest%20American%20metropolitan%20areas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20paid%2034%25%20more%20to%20live%20in%20walkable%20neighborhoods%2C%20while%20renters%20paid%2041%25%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20study%20found%20no%20significant%20correlation%20between%20the%20type%20of%20housing%20someone%20lives%20in%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0whether%20it's%20an%20apartment%20or%20a%20detached%20single-family%20house%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20their%20wellbeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20just%20as%20likely%20to%20be%20happy%20in%20single-family%20homes%2C%20as%20in%20townhomes%2C%20as%20in%20apartment%20towers%2C%26quot%3B%20Cleveland%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20levels%20of%20density%20are%20compatible%20%E2%80%94%20in%20different%20ways%20for%20different%20reasons%20%E2%80%94%20with%20happiness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20exceptions%20to%20this%20were%20basement%20apartments%20and%20very%20small%20units.%20Living%20in%20a%20basement%20unit%20was%20associated%20with%20fewer%20social%20connections%20and%20relationships%20with%20neighbors%20while%20living%20in%20an%20apartment%20smaller%20than%20300%20square%20feet%20was%20associated%20with%20worse%20general%20well-being%2C%20even%20when%20controlling%20for%20income%2C%20ownership%20status%2C%20the%20number%20of%20amenities%2C%20and%20other%20factors%2C%20the%20study%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20found%20that%20many%20large%20towers%20with%20smaller%20units%20were%20designed%20for%20lower-income%20residents%20and%20didn't%20have%20as%20much%20access%20to%20community%20spaces%20and%20amenities.%20These%20findings%20are%20important%20for%20city%20planners%20and%20builders%20to%20understand%2C%20so%20they%20can%20incorporate%20design%20elements%20that%20promote%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20designing%20these%20small%20units%2C%20which%20we%20know%20are%20housing%20our%20most%20vulnerable%20residents%2C%20and%20there%20are%20no%20protections%20around%20making%20sure%20that%20they%20are%20well-connected%20to%20community%20amenities%2C%20they%20have%20social%20spaces%20in%20the%20building%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0if%20those%20things%20aren't%20accounted%20for%2C%20then%20we%20risk%20building%20these%20small%20units%20that%20further%20negatively%20impacts%20people's%20well-being%2C%26quot%3B%20Hebert%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20articl