3Cp%3EGrossman%20described%20himself%20as%20having%20%26quot%3B12%20second%20acts%2C%26quot%3B%20holding%20jobs%20as%20a%20school%20teacher%2C%20computer%20tech%20support%2C%20business%20sales%2C%20corporate%20communications%2C%20and%20a%20toy%20store%20owner%20%E2%80%94%20and%20each%20of%20those%20employment%20opportunities%20has%20brought%20him%20to%20Pennsylvania%2C%20Texas%2C%20California%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20now%20Seattle%2C%20where%20he%20currently%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20moving%20around%20has%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20him%20to%20maintain%20relationships.%20Additionally%2C%20growing%20up%20as%20a%20gay%20man%20on%20the%20autistic%20spectrum%2C%20Grossman%20said%20it%20was%20harder%20for%20him%20to%20find%20a%20community%20he%20felt%20he%20could%20belong%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20gay%20people%20at%20my%20age%20had%20major%20issues%20with%20their%20families%20growing%20up%20and%20have%20completely%20separated%2C%20whether%20their%20families%20threw%20them%20out%20or%20whether%20they%20couldn't%20accept%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Grossman%20said.%20%26quot%3BThings%20are%20different%20in%20the%20future%2C%20but%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20single%20people%20in%20the%20LGBTQIA%20community%20who%20don't%20have%20the%20support%20and%20friendships%20that%20they%20need.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20all%20changed%20about%20three%20years%20ago.%20Grossman%20was%20struggling%20to%20find%20friends%20in%20Seattle%2C%20and%20while%20he%20tried%20to%20join%20groups%20to%20meet%20new%20people%2C%20nothing%20seemed%20to%20stick.%20But%20when%20someone%20mentioned%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwiderhorizonsvillage.org%2Fa-virtual-village%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bsenior%20village%26quot%3B%20in%20Seattle%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20him%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20give%20it%20a%20shot.%20Since%20then%2C%20he's%20found%20a%20community%20and%20formed%20close%20friendships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvtvnetwork.org%2Fcontent.aspx%3Fpage_id%3D22%26club_id%3D691012%26module_id%3D248578%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESenior%20villages%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20a%20nationwide%20network%20of%20community-based%20nonprofits%20that%20connect%20older%20adults%20to%20others%20in%20their%20area%20through%20resources%20and%20activities.%20There%20are%20over%20400%20senior%20villages%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20they're%20unique%20in%20that%20in%20contrast%20to%20a%20retirement%20community%2C%20these%20villages%20allow%20older%20adults%20to%20live%20where%20they%20choose%20while%20still%20having%20access%20to%20virtual%20and%20in-person%20resources%20that%20the%20village%20offers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20suddenly%20a%20lot%20of%20opportunities%20and%20activities%20that%20I%20can%20rely%20upon%20and%20be%20with%20people%2C%20and%20there%20are%20people%20who%20know%20me%20and%20care%20about%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Grossman.%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20I%20were%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20something%20and%20didn't%20go%2C%20someone%20would%20call%20me%20and%20say%2C%20'what%20happened%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvtvnetwork.clubexpress.com%2Fcontent.aspx%3Fpage_id%3D22%26club_id%3D691012%26module_id%3D241346%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enetwork%20of%20sponsors%3C%2Fa%3E%20funds%20senior%20villages%2C%20and%20members%20of%20the%20villages%20can%20pay%20from%20%24150%20to%20%24425%20a%20year%2C%20depending%20on%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etheir%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elevel%20of%20involvement.%20For%20Grossman%2C%20the%20cost%20is%20well%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20times%20when%20I%20would've%20just%20stayed%20home%20alone%2C%20and%20now%20I%20will%20do%20some%20of%20the%20things%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20before%2C%20like%20go%20to%20the%20movies%20or%20to%20dinner%2C%26quot%3B%20Grossman%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20a%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'We%20need%20to%20be%20more%20concerned%20about%20other%20people'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmodern-loneliness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELoneliness%20is%20something%20that's%20hit%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20ages%20especially%20hard%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20In%20May%2C%20US%20Surgeon%20General%20Vivek%20Murthy%20described%20the%20issue%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bepidemic%20of%20loneliness%20and%20isolation%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20could%20have%20detrimental%20effects%20on%20a%20person's%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%20if%20it%20goes%20unresolved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Gen%20Zers%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-loneliness-spends-money-to-make-friends-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espent%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emoney%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20a%20range%20of%20activities%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20meet%20new%20people%20and%20form%20friendships%2C%20but%20seniors%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etend%20to%20have%20fewer%20options.%20A%20University%20of%20Michigan%20National%20Poll%20on%20Healthy%20Aging%20January%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthyagingpoll.org%2Freports-more%2Freport%2Ftrends-loneliness-among-older-adults-2018-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20one-in-three%20adults%20aged%2050%20to%2080%20reported%20feeling%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrossman%20said%20it%20needs%20to%20be%20talked%20about%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20COVID%20hit%20and%20everyone%20isolated%2C%20that's%20when%20I%20became%20more%20aware%20that%20I%20really%20needed%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20if%20I%20were%20to%20fall%20down%20and%20get%20hurt%20in%20here%3F%20Who%20would%20know%2C%20and%20how%20long%20would%20it%20take%3F%20And%20if%20I%20go%20out%20and%20buy%20something%20on%20sale%20and%20get%20too%20much%20of%20it%20at%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20I%20would%20like%20to%20be%20able%20to%20share%20that%20with%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Grossman%20continued.%20%26quot%3BSo%20just%20all%20of%20those%20things%20helped%20me%20realize%20that%20living%20as%20a%20single%20was%20very%20isolating.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESenior%20villages%20are%20one%20way%20older%20adults%20can%20become%20involved%20in%20a%20community%20to%20meet%20others.%20The%20Village%20to%20Village%20Network%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvtvnetwork.clubexpress.com%2Fcontent.aspx%3Fpage_id%3D1905%26club_id%3D691012%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresource%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20allows%20those%20interested%20to%20search%20for%20villages%20in%20their%20area%20they%20could%20join.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20other%20older%20adults%20are%20working%20on%20innovative%20ways%20to%20form%20connections%20later%20in%20life.%20BI%20previously%20spoke%20to%20Joe%20Lamy%2C%20a%2075-year-old%20retiree%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-crisis-retiree-how-to-achieve-happiness-budget-retirement-seniors-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewho%20started%20biweekly%20groups%20at%20a%20senior%20center%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20people%20can%20simply%20sit%20in%20a%20room%20and%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20at%20no%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrossman%20said%20he's%20hopeful%20that%20the%20government%20will%20take%20more%20steps%20to%20address%20the%20loneliness%20epidemic%20and%20pay%20more%20attention%20to%20the%20challenges%20older%20adults%20are%20facing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20about%20being%20a%20human%20being%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20be%20more%20concerned%20about%20other%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Grossman%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20just%20abandon%20people%20when%20they%20age.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20found%20a%20solution%20to%20loneliness%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenior-villages-loneliness-making-friends-in-retirement-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707045421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bd296c7a3d27148877343b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenior-villages-loneliness-making-friends-in-retirement-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rick%20Grossman%20has%20moved%20around%20most%20of%20his%20life%2C%20and%20he's%20found%20it%20hard%20to%20maintain%20relationships.%20That%20all%20changed%20when%20he%20found%20a%20%26quot%3Bsenior%20village.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenior-villages-loneliness-making-friends-in-retirement-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Disastrous%20Origins%20of%20Sex%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164413%2FSnowball_Huronian.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20life%203.8%20billion%20years%20ago%20was%20relatively%20simple.%20They%20were%20creatures%20known%20as%20prokaryotes%3A%20single-celled%20microscopic%20organisms%20where%20DNA%20strands%20floated%20openly%20around%20the%20cell%2C%20increasing%20the%20risk%20of%20it%20getting%20damaged.%20But%20they%20survived%2C%20and%20the%20bottom%20of%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20oceans%20began%20to%20become%20overcrowded%20with%20living%20little%20blobs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20297px)%2085vw%2C%20297px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164013%2FThe-Shortest-History-of-Sex-front-cover.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22297%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164013%2FThe-Shortest-History-of-Sex-front-cover.jpg%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164013%2FThe-Shortest-History-of-Sex-front-cover-196x300.jpg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164013%2FThe-Shortest-History-of-Sex-front-cover-667x1024.jpg%20667w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695683%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22456%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Shortest%20History%20of%20Sex%2C%20David%20Baker%2C%20Pan%20Macmillan%20India%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20overcome%20the%20shortage%20of%20%E2%80%98real%20estate%E2%80%99%203.4%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20some%20prokaryotes%20evolved%20to%20live%20near%20the%20surface%20of%20the%20oceans%2C%20no%20longer%20keeping%20themselves%20warm%20with%20underwater%20volcanoes.%20Instead%2C%20these%20new%20microscopic%20blobs%20evolved%20to%20use%20the%20Sun%E2%80%99s%20energy.%20They%20used%20photosynthesis%2C%20converting%20water%2C%20sunlight%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20(CO2)%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20to%20feed%20themselves.%20Just%20like%20plants%20today.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20just%20like%20plants%20today%2C%20they%20pumped%20oxygen%20(O2)%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20as%20a%20waste%20product.%20The%20problem%20is%20that%20oxygen%20is%20highly%20turbulent%2C%20can%20create%20violent%20chemical%20reactions%20and%20in%20large%20quantities%20could%20kill%20fragile%20primitive%20life%20like%20those%20ancestral%20microbes%20that%20had%20evolved%20on%20an%20early%20Earth%20where%20there%20was%20very%20little%20oxygen%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202.5%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20microscopic%20photosynthesisers%20had%20increased%20the%20level%20of%20oxygen%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20from%20next%20to%20nothing%20to%202.5%20per%20cent.%20This%20nasty%20chemical%20killed%20off%20scores%20of%20microbes%20in%20an%20event%20known%20as%20the%20Oxygen%20Holocaust%2C%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20first%20known%20mass%20extinction%20event%20and%20one%20of%20the%20only%20mass%20extinction%20events%20(before%20humans)%20kicked%20off%20by%20living%20organisms%20rather%20than%20an%20asteroid%20impact%20or%20a%20super-volcanic%20eruption.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20surviving%20microbes%20evolved%20an%20increasing%20tolerance%20for%20oxygen%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%20Some%20of%20them%20even%20evolved%20the%20ability%20to%20consume%20oxygen%20instead%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20reversing%20which%20chemical%20was%20food%20and%20which%20waste.%20These%20were%20the%20first%20aerobic%20species%2C%20microscopic%20creatures%20similar%20in%20that%20respect%20to%20humans%20and%20other%20animals.%20We%20inhale%20oxygen%2C%20we%20exhale%20carbon%20dioxide.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20photosynthesisers%20remained%20the%20majority%20of%20living%20things%20on%20Earth%20and%20continued%20to%20create%20unmitigated%20disasters%20by%20pumping%20out%20oxygen.%20Enough%20O2%20had%20gathered%20in%20the%20atmosphere%202.2%20billion%20years%20ago%20that%20the%20oxygen%20atoms%20began%20to%20group%20together%20in%20threes%2C%20creating%20ozone%20(O3).%20The%20resulting%20ozone%20layer%20that%20blanketed%20Earth%20reflected%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20Sun%E2%80%99s%20rays%20back%20into%20space.%20While%20we%20desperately%20require%20the%20ozone%20layer%20to%20protect%20us%20from%20solar%20radiation%20today%2C%20in%20the%20short%20term%202.2%20billion%20years%20ago%2C%20this%20was%20not%20a%20good%20thing.%20Photosynthesising%20life%20continued%20to%20increase%20the%20thickness%20of%20the%20ozone%20layer.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20Earth%20got%20colder%20and%20colder.%20The%20oceans%20froze%20at%20the%20poles.%20Then%20the%20ice%20spread%20down%20towards%20the%20equator%2C%20encasing%20the%20entire%20planet%20in%20a%20frozen%20prison%2C%20in%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98Snowball%20Earth%E2%80%99%20event%2C%20roughly%202%20billion%20years%20ago.%20The%20average%20global%20temperature%20would%20have%20been%20around%20-50%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESnowball%20Earth%20imposed%20a%20strain%20on%20the%20microbes%20living%20in%20the%20now%20ice-covered%20oceans.%20As%20a%20result%20of%20the%20strain%2C%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20microbe%20evolved%3A%20the%20eukaryote.%20These%20are%20%E2%80%98beefier%E2%80%99%20cells%2C%2010%20to%201000%20times%20the%20size%20of%20prokaryotes%2C%20which%20also%20evolved%20to%20protect%20their%20DNA%20by%20keeping%20it%20in%20a%20central%20nucleus%20instead%20of%20letting%20the%20strands%20just%20float%20around%20the%20cell.%20We%20humans%20are%20descended%20from%20these%20eukaryotes%2C%20as%20are%20all%20the%20ancestors%20and%20descendants%20in%20the%20evolutionary%20tree%20of%20the%20plant%20and%20animal%20kingdoms.%20And%20it%20is%20these%20tiny%20eukaryotic%20blobs%20that%20were%20the%20first%20creatures%20to%20have%20sex.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20same%20disastrous%20Snowball%20Earth%20period%2C%20these%20microscopic%20eukaryotes%20began%20to%20engage%20in%20carnal%20relations%20with%20one%20another%20%E2%80%93%20as%20does%2099.9%20per%20cent%20of%20all%20eukaryotic%20life%20today.%20The%20habit%20stuck%20and%20has%20grown%20only%20more%20thrilling%20and%20perplexing.%20But%20the%20question%20of%20how%20and%20why%20our%20microbial%20ancestors%20began%20to%20feel%20compelled%20to%20exchange%20genetic%20information%2C%20in%20the%20same%20way%20two%20people%20might%20exchange%20phone%20numbers%20at%20a%20bar%2C%20remains%20shrouded%20in%20mystery.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20above%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Shortest%20History%20of%20Sex%2C%3Cem%3E%20an%20exploration%20of%20sexual%20evolution%2C%20tracing%20it%20from%20approximately%20two%20billion%20years%20ago%20until%20the%20present%20time%2C%20by%20David%20Baker.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDavid%20Baker%20is%20a%20history%20and%20science%20writer.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707045382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F04164413%2FSnowball_Huronian.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-disastrous-origins-of-sex%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20disastrous%20Snowball%20Earth%20period%2C%20microscopic%20eukaryotes%20began%20to%20engage%20in%20carnal%20relations%20with%20one%20another.%20For%20some%20reason%2C%20the%20habit%20stuck.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-disastrous-origins-of-sex%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20tried%20the%20perfect%20space%20meal%20for%20astronauts%2C%20and%20it%20was%20surprisingly%20flavorful%20and%20easy%20to%20make%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20salad%20containing%20sweet%20potatoes%2C%20kale%2C%20and%20barley%20on%20a%20rainbow-striped%20plate.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bd3b716fcb546d2d4bb951%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EEmily%20Swaim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAstronauts%20need%20more%20calories%20and%20nutrients%20than%20someone%20on%20Earth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20packaged%20food%20loses%20nutritional%20value%20in%20space%2C%20so%20what%20will%20humans%20eat%20on%20long%20space%20missions%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EScientists%20figured%20out%20the%20best%20meal%20for%20astronauts%20and%20it's%20worth%20trying%20for%20yourself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2F