cipe%20is%20designed%20to%20meet%20the%20nutritional%20value%20for%20three%20male%20astronauts%2C%20offering%20each%20one%20about%20900%20calories%20per%20serving.%20Here's%20a%20list%20of%20the%20ingredients%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20need%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E642%20grams%20of%20sweet%20potato%20(about%205%20small%20potatoes)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E223%20grams%20of%20pearled%20barley%20(about%201%20cup)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E155%20grams%20of%20poppy%20seeds%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E79%20grams%20of%20kale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E63%20grams%20of%20soybeans%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E25%20grams%20of%20peanuts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E18%20grams%20of%20sunflower%20seeds%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20astronaut%20would%20ideally%20eat%20this%20meal%20once%20a%20week%20as%20part%20of%20a%20rotation%20of%20dishes%2C%20said%20study%20co-author%20Volker%20Hessel%2C%20who's%20a%20professor%20of%20sustainable%20chemical%20engineering%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Adelaide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20definitely%20see%20myself%20eating%20the%20space%20salad%20that%20often.%20The%20salad%20was%20easy%20to%20make%20and%20took%20about%2030%20minutes%20from%20prep%20to%20plate.%20Plus%2C%20all%20that%20protein%20made%20it%20filling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELong%20space%20flights%20require%20special%20diets%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221216%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20artist's%20illustration%20of%20an%20astronaut%20on%20Mars%20waving%20at%20a%20camera.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655df9cf9c7d23cb3b9e9ad1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22601%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20artist's%20illustration%20shows%20an%20astronaut%20streaming%20from%20Mars.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FLacey%20Young%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20authors%20developed%20the%20space%20salad%20based%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fift.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1111%2Fj.1750-3841.2010.01982.x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENASA's%20nutritional%20guidelines%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20long%20space%20voyages%2C%20using%20computers%20to%20calculate%20the%20most%20nutritious%2C%20resource-efficient%20combination.%20Business%20Insider%20reached%20out%20to%20NASA's%20Space%20Food%20Systems%20Laboratory%20for%20comment%20but%20it%20didn't%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20more%20energy%2C%20astronauts%20will%20also%20need%20more%20of%20certain%20vitamins%20like%20calcium%20and%20magnesium%20%E2%80%94%20to%20prevent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-travel-effects-human-body-nasa-2017-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eastronauts'%20skeletons%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20wasting%20away%20in%20zero%20gravity.%20They'll%20also%20need%20potassium%20for%20homeostasis%2C%20which%20balances%20and%20stabilizes%20all%20the%20body's%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20thankfully%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffpls.2020.00199%2Ffull%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresearch%20from%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20the%20nutritional%20content%20of%20crops%20grown%20in%20space%20is%20usually%20close%20to%20that%20of%20their%20Earth-bound%20cousins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20we%20can%20calculate%20approximately%20how%20much%20nutrition%20astronauts%20would%20earn%20from%20eating%20this%20space%20salad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20one%20serving%20of%20the%20space%20salad%20has%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E52%20g%20of%20poppy%20seeds%2C%20which%20carry%20749%20mg%20of%20calcium%20(62%25%20of%20recommended%20daily%20intake%20for%20astronauts%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E214%20g%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdiet-nutrition%2Ffoods-high-in-potassium%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esweet%20potatoes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20offer%20807%20mg%20potassium%20(17%25%20of%20daily%20intake)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E74%20g%20of%20barley%20that%20provides%2016%20mg%20of%20magnesium%20(4%25%20of%20daily%20intake)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20of%20course%2C%20not%20every%20astronaut%20is%20going%20to%20need%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-astronauts-food-season-liquid-salt-pepper-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexactly%20the%20same%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFuture%20research%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222412%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20water%20bubble%20floats%20in%20front%20of%20NASA%20Leland%20Melvin%20on%20the%20space%20shuttle%20Atlantis%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652076826e038039826c702e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstronaut%20Leland%20Melvin%20looks%20at%20a%20floating%20water%20bubble%20on%20the%20middeck%20of%20space%20shuttle%20Atlantis.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scenarios%20in%20the%20study%20were%20designed%20for%20male%20astronauts%2C%20alone.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-artemis-missions-first-black-astronaut-woman-canadian-to-moon-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFemale%20astronauts%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20likely%20have%20different%20requirements%20for%20nutrients%20like%20magnesium%20and%20iron.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20authors%20said%20they%20plan%20to%20adjust%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmediterrean-diet-healthiest-best-overall-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediet%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20include%20female%20astronauts%20in%20future%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20things%20even%20more%20challenging%2C%20Hessel%20said%20each%20team%20member's%20body%20will%20react%20differently%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fejections-from-sun-may-threaten-future-moon-missions-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estresses%20of%20space%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20an%20astronaut's%20dietary%20needs%20may%20change%20during%20the%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20when%20an%20astronaut%20spends%20an%20hour%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-shows-cosmonaut-space-littering-during-spacewalk-nasa-says-harmless-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutside%20the%20ISS%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20perform%20an%20extravehicular%20activity%2C%20NASA's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fntrs.nasa.gov%2Fapi%2Fcitations%2F20205008306%2Fdownloads%2FJSC67378%2520Expl%2520Nutr%2520Reqs%2520042020.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2020%20nutritional%20guidelines%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20recommend%20they%20eat%20an%20extra%20200%20calories%20that%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20computer%20simulations%20in%20the%20study%20should%20be%20able%20to%20craft%20new%20diets%20as%20needed.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20give%20recommendations%20for%20new%20requirements%20virtually%20the%20same%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Hessel%20said.%20But%20a%20shuttle's%20food%20supply%20will%20need%20to%20be%20flexible%20enough%20to%20account%20for%20these%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20about%20meat%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22lab-grown%20meat%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60ffda80f350d500195919fe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221278%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELab-grown%20meat%20might%20one%20day%20be%20a%20way%20to%20feed%20astronauts%20on%20deep-space%20missions.%20%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMeat-lovers%20don't%20need%20to%20worry%3A%20the%20future%20of%20space%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20vegetarian.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronaut-food-in-space-timeline-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPast%20astronaut%20meals%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20included%20dehydrated%20shrimp%20cocktail%2C%20beef%20brisket%2C%20and%20even%20teriyaki%20chicken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFuture%20space%20explorers%20may%20also%20eat%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flab-grown-caviar-meat-biotech-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elab-grown%20meat%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20FDA%20approval%20process%20and%20may%20soon%20be%20available%20in%20restaurants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20also%20working%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffspas.2021.699097%2Ffull%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eraising%20fish%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20space%20so%20astronauts%20can%20have%20fresh%20meat.%20The%20study%20authors%20say%20fish%20could%20be%20an%20ideal%20part%20of%20a%20space%20ecosystem%2C%20since%20astronauts%20could%20feed%20them%20excess%20plant%20material%20and%20then%20harvest%20their%20droppings%20for%20fertilizer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20wanted%20to%20add%20meat%20to%20your%20space%20salad%2C%20I'd%20recommend%20pairing%20it%20with%20a%20lighter%20option%20such%20as%20chicken%20or%20tuna.%20But%20if%20your%20astronaut%20heart%20yearns%20for%20more%20exploration%2C%20you%20could%20try%20any%20salad%20additions%20you%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-meal-for-astronauts-review-recipe-photos-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707045181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bd57d543bb77284ba339a2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-meal-for-astronauts-review-recipe-photos-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Scientists%20designed%20the%20