e'd%20have%20the%20option%20of%20using%20his%20first%20name%20if%20he%20wanted.%20He%20was%20called%20Alex%20by%20everyone%20for%20many%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe%20chose%20to%20go%20by%20his%20first%20name%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20high%20school%2C%20Alex%20was%20composing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblasting-classical-music-in-train-stations-is-music-torture-composer-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclassical%20music%3C%2Fa%3E%20seriously.%20At%20a%20conference%20for%20Presidential%20Scholars%20during%20his%20senior%20year%2C%20he%20spontaneously%20decided%20that%20Sheridan%20Seyfried%20was%20a%20more%20%26quot%3Bcomposerly%26quot%3B%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20whole%20week%2C%20he%20introduced%20himself%20that%20way%20to%20hundreds%20of%20people.%20When%20he%20returned%20home%2C%20he%20announced%20that%20he%20would%20rather%20not%20be%20called%20Alex%20anymore.%20I%20assumed%20we'd%20forget%20frequently%2C%20as%20it%20was%20such%20a%20very%20old%20habit.%20But%20our%20son%20had%20an%20ingenious%20way%20to%20teach%20our%20family%3A%20he%20just%20stopped%20responding%20when%20we%20called%20him%20by%20his%20old%20name.%20Alex%20didn't%20hear%20us%20when%20it%20was%20time%20to%20empty%20the%20trash%3B%20as%20soon%20as%20Sheridan%20was%20asked%2C%20the%20chore%20was%20done%20immediately.%20Within%20days%2C%20we%20were%20perfectly%20trained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20forget%20we%20ever%20called%20him%20Alex%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESheridan%20became%20a%20professional%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fbenefits-of-music%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclassical%20composer%3C%2Fa%3E%20whose%20works%20are%20performed%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20He%20has%20fully%20embraced%20his%20first%20name%20for%20more%20than%2020%20years%20now%2C%20and%20we%20tend%20to%20forget%20he%20was%20ever%20called%20Alex.%20But%20some%20people%20in%20our%20lives%20still%20refer%20to%20him%20by%20his%20middle%20name%20%E2%80%94%20often%20his%20classmates%20and%20teachers%20from%20early%20school%20years.%20It%20doesn't%20bother%20him%20%E2%80%94%20or%20us%20%E2%80%94%20a%20bit%2C%20and%20it%20actually%20brings%20back%20some%20fond%20memories%20of%20his%20childhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowadays%2C%20unusual%20seems%20to%20be%20usual%2C%20as%20parents%20are%20giving%20their%20children%20a%20huge%20variety%20of%20first%20names%2C%20many%20used%20by%20all%20genders.%20I%20think%20it's%20a%20wonderful%20development%2C%20reflecting%20a%20time%20when%20imagination%20and%20individual%20expression%20are%20highly%20valued.%20I%20love%20encountering%20a%20new-to-me%20name%2C%20and%20learning%20the%20story%20of%20that%20name.%20Granted%2C%20it%20may%20be%20harder%20to%20spell%20these%20more%20offbeat%20names%2C%20than%20it%20was%20to%20spell%20the%20names%20of%20the%20four%20Kevins%20and%20five%20Debbies%20who%20were%20in%20my%20first%20grade%20class%2C%20back%20in%20the%20day.%20Some%20may%20still%20prefer%20more%20common%20names%20for%20their%20offspring%2C%20and%20that's%20fine%20too.%20But%20people%20can%20learn%2C%20and%20are%20learning%2C%20that%20there%20are%20countless%20choices%20when%20it's%20time%20to%20name%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20our%20family%2C%20I'll%20always%20be%20glad%20we%20carried%20on%20the%20Sheridan%20tradition.%20Now%2C%20if%20only%20my%20mom%20had%20spelled%20my%20name%20Elyse%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalled-son-using-common-middle-name-prevent-teasing-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707044881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b9657e43bb77284ba1e573%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalled-son-using-common-middle-name-prevent-teasing-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20mother%20named%20her%20son%20Sherida