%2C%20right%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20don't%20think%20I'm%20alone%20in%20that%20%E2%80%94%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20many%20people%20have%20been%20concerned%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20was%20on%20the%20precipice%20of%20a%20breakdown.%20Heck%2C%20the%20conventional%20wisdom%20was%20that%20unemployment%20had%20to%20spike%20in%20order%20to%20bring%20inflation%20down.%20But%20after%20Friday's%20jobs%20report%2C%20and%20given%20trends%20in%20employment%20and%20inflation%20last%20year%2C%20that%20notion%20is%20starting%20to%20look%20a%20little%20silly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20just%20because%20there%20hasn't%20been%20a%20sudden%20spike%20in%20unemployment%20doesn't%20mean%20it's%20an%20ideal%20moment%20to%20hop%20to%20a%20different%20job%20or%20bank%20on%20HR%20being%20terrified%20to%20lose%20you%20if%20they%20don't%20give%20the%20fat%20raise%20you%20requested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20case%20that%20%3Cem%3Enothing%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecan%20turn%20the%20current%20situation%20negative%2C%20and%20if%20and%20when%20things%20do%20turn%20negative%2C%20they%20may%20turn%20quite%20fast.%20But%20right%20now%2C%20they're%20just%20not%20turning%2C%20at%20least%20not%20in%20a%20way%20that%20should%20keep%20workers%20up%20at%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjanuary-jobs-report-labor-market-good-economy-inflation-wages-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707044162000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bd4f3843bb77284ba33474%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessins